manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Rubbermaid 4-Tier Shoe Shelf The Perfect Organizer in Any Space The Rubbermaid 4-Tier Shoe Shelf is a complementary storage solution that fits in any space in your home. Engineered with durable metal and featuring an anti-snag chrome finish, this shelving system is perfect for organizing all types of footwear. It is easy to assemble with no tools. Quality that Speaks for Itself For nearly 100 years, Rubbermaid has been a leader in high-quality, innovative products that help simplify life. At Rubbermaid, we believe that products should work well, while looking great. Craftmanship matters and details like color, material and finish all add up. Rubbermaid is committed to delivering great-looking long-lasting products that consumers can depend on. Features & Benefits Large capacity Easy to assemble Versatile use Raised back lip Durable metal construction

Product Features Simple Storage Tapered shelving design allows for quick grab and go of stored items to keep closets, doorways, and mudrooms clutter-free. Floor Protection Non-slip rubber foot pads keep shelves from moving, as well as prevents damage to floors. Raised Back Lip The raised side and back shelving lips ensure shelved shoes don't fall over or off of the shelf, no matter the size.

Lightweight and Easy to Move Durable handles and lightweight metal provide an easy-to-move solution to effortlessly clean under or around. Easy to Clean The powder-coated finish can be easily wiped down with non –abrasive common household cleaners. Keeps Odors Away Ventilated shelving allows for increased airflow and breathability for stored footwear and items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Assembly tip, PLEASE LOOK at photo
reviews.reviewText: This is actually a great little cart, and it’s actually very sturdy IF you snap the parts together correctly. The only real problem is that the directions suck so badly, because there’s a key piece of info that is not made clear, as can be seen in so many of the reviews here.Please look at the accompanying photo and note that the hooks go OVER each little rail, but the center nib has to go UNDER it.It’s easy to do because all you have to do is pull the bottom rail out a little (it’s flexible) and pop the nib under it. No tools are needed, just your fingers.Hope this helps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good organizer for a case of water bottles but instructions bite
reviews.reviewText: You almost need to be an octopus to put this thing together but it is sturdy and holding together for some time now. I saw the idea on Pinterest and wanted an easier way to clean around any cases without having to actually keep hauling the case around. My husband is someone skilled at putting things together but I think he was close to having me send this one back. The paper instructions in the box were frustrating and after he was done he had this to say. The instructions on the outside of the actual box was so much clearer and he wished he seen that first !!!

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Frustrating to put together
reviews.reviewText: Takes forever to setup, definitely not as easy to break down and setup like I was hoping. Because I can't click the pieces together all the way, it's not hard for to accidentally have it fall apart. If it clicked together easier, I could see this being sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works as advertised
reviews.reviewText: I included the measurements in my pictures as they weren't in the product pictures. You can use the "See in my room" but I used it and it looked like there would be room on each side of the rack but you can see in the pictures it barely fits in my space. I had to push my washer and dryer over to get it in the space.There are no tools needed to put this together, the shelves just sit on top of the sides. You will need to lean one side up against something to get the first shelf on.It does have a rubber coating so it's durable and waterproof if the bottom on your shoes are wet. I did have to leave one shelf out to get my boots on but if you are just using it for regular flat shoes you can utilize all 4 shelves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A pain! But.
reviews.reviewText: I liked it so much I bought another.I want to address the elephant in the room though. This is/was a huge pain to set up. The first time was terrible, trying to figure out how much finagling was necessary to get everything to stay together. To say it's a labor of love is probably spot on. The second time around, no sweat (maybe a little).The main issue is the little plastic connectors are all held by friction, and because of that, you really got to mash those bad boys down. I figured out the best way the second time around. You loosely attach 3 or so panels together and flip what you have around, and mash the connectors down with a rag-to-hand barrier.With that out of the way, they're just so versatile. Rather than make a 2x3, I just have two separate ones that I can pick up and move around when it's most convenient. They hold a fair amount of both weight and volume, and they're not bad to look at surprisingly. Love em.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not sturdy, wobbles. Supposed to be easy to put together, but very time-consuming.
reviews.reviewText: It's metal, and is what the description says it is, but BE WARE! This thing is not meant to be a shelf for anything. On a level hard surface floor, this thing wobbles as if it is in a constant earthquake. Feels shifty, and cheap when you touch it. I'm fare at assembling furniture. And this thing is fairly straight forward as far as directions for assembly. BUT, the screws are almost too small to fit into the holes, and I recommend a power drill to actually bolt the screws down, I think a normal screwdriver would be more work than what is already required of this flimsy thing. lOOK AROUND AND FIND SOMETHING BETTER FOR YOUR MONEY.
